vulnerability.name: USN-6047-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that the Traffic-Control Index (TCINDEX) implementation in the Linux kernel did not properly perform filter deactivation in some situations. A local attacker could possibly use this to gain elevated privileges. Please note that with the fix for this CVE, kernel support for the TCINDEX classifier has been removed.

statements.status_notes: The system could be made to run programs as an administrator.
